50|$|<b>Neurosyphilis</b> is an {{infection}} of the brain or spinal cord caused by the spirochete Treponema pallidum. It usually occurs in {{people who have had}} chronic, untreated syphilis, usually about 10 to 20 years after first infection and develops in about 25%-40% of persons who are not treated. The United States' Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) advises that <b>neurosyphilis</b> can occur at any stage of a syphilis infection.|$|E
